Vintage-style illustration of an intricate mechanical switchboard with brass gears and copper wiring, where multiple ornate Victorian-era machines with glowing glass dials are connected through an elaborate network of cables and pneumatic tubes converging at a central octagonal hub. Each machine displays different miniature dioramas behind glass panels - one showing tiny figures working at desks, another displaying flowing data streams represented as colored liquids in tubes, a third with mechanical clockwork calculations. The central hub pulses with warm amber light, routing connections between the disparate machines. Muted sepia tones with pops of copper, emerald, and burgundy. Steam wisps curl around the edges, and small indicator lights blink throughout the complex apparatus.
